column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
The inattentive culinarian dearly hopes his international delivery hasn't been lost at sea.
Speak with the diligent deckhand.
Pick up the shipment for Aunt Tii's.
Deliver the shipment for Aunt Tii's to the inattentive culinarian.
Speak with the inattentive culinarian.
You were on the ship that pulled into port just now, were you not? I've a favor to ask.
I'm expecting a shipment addressed to Aunt Tii's Tacos, but I fear it may have been unloaded on the southern pier by mistake. I'd be ever so grateful if you could speak with your crew for me.
I need to be getting back to open the shop, but if you do manage to find it, please bring it over. I'll see to it you're paid for the delivery, I promise!
A shipment for Aunt Tii's? Got it right here, o' course. Not sure what you were told, but all imports from Eorzea are unloaded on this side.
That culinarian makes some great tacos, but I'll be damned if he can pay attention to half the words I say to him...
His order's packed and ready in that crate there, but bugger me if it ain't heavy.
Carry the shipment to the inattentive culinarian at Aunt Tii's Tacos before the time runs out.
You will have 120 seconds to complete the task. Should you fail, return to the starting location and begin anew.
Right, that's the crate for Aunt Tii's. It's not far from here, if you don't mind carryin' it over.
What'd I tell you? Remember, lift with your legs!
You haven't found my shipment? Could you try asking around?
You found it! Thank the gods. I don't know what I would have done had my cookbooks been left on the dock back in Limsa Lominsa.
What luck that I could flag down such a hospitable deckhand.
Wait─what do you mean, you're not part of the crew!? I thought you came into port with my books!

Our taco stand gets a lot of tourists, so I thought I'd import some cookbooks from your culinary capital and brush up on foreign food culture. Who knows─one of these days I might just invent an Eorzean-style taco!
Anyway, my apologies for the misunderstanding! As payment, take these freshly made tacos, on the house!
